{"lemma":"دَسَمٌ","slug":"دَسَمٌ","root":"د.س.م","root_slug":"د-س-م","root_link":"/words/roots/د-س-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12548"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obturate, to block up, to lock up, to stuff"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to besmear, to efface, to obliterate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have much fat, to be greasy, to drip of lard"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make greasy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَسِمَ (dasima) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fat, grease, adeps"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fatty, greasy, creamy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rich, succulent, substantial etc., much that nurtures the body or mind","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"common plural of أَدْسَم (ʔadsam, “greasy”)","tags":["common","form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12548","headword_ar":"دَسَمٌ","root":"dsm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadakN","text_ar":"وَدَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) both signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dripping that exudes from flesh-meat and from fat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wdk","text_ar":"ودك"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadak","text_ar":"وَدَك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of flesh-meat and of fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaraku","text_ar":"الوَرَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwadaku","text_ar":"الوَدَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or, accord. to the T,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wadak","text_ar":"وَدَك"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of flesh-meat and of fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasomN","text_ar":"دَسْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasamN","text_ar":"دَسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to El-Kurtubee; but El-Welee El-'Irákee says, I have not seen this on the authority of any other lexicologist. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaduhu mina Ald~asami saliTapN","text_ar":"يَدُهُ مِنَ الدَّسَمِ سَلِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning, if correctly transcribed,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His hand is hard by reason of dirt"},{"kind":"text","text":"adhering to it: in my MS. copy of the K, the last word is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTilapN","text_ar":"سَطِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; a word which I do not find in any sense: in the TK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sTlp","text_ar":"سطلة"},{"kind":"text","text":": this Freytag thinks to be the right reading, though I know of no such word; and he renders the phrase, “ manus ejus propter sordes inhaerentes catinus est; ” evidently assuming that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sTlp","text_ar":"سطلة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTolN","text_ar":"سَطْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [It seems that you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA fiyhi dasamN","text_ar":"مَا فِيهِ دَسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, any profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a sense assigned in the TA to the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA fyh","text_ar":"ما فيه"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dysm dsm","text_ar":"ديسم دسم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which I think it evident that the transcriber has written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dysm","text_ar":"ديسم"},{"kind":"text","text":"by mistake, and forgotten to erase it after adding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dsm","text_ar":"دسم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Accord. to IAar, it means also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru Al*~ikori","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ الذِّكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Praising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glorifying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"God,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; a sense in which it is incorrectly said in the K to be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasiymN","text_ar":"دَسِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyrN","text_ar":"اَمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and hence the trad., of weak authority,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA ya*okuruwna A@ll~`ha A_il~aA dasamFA","text_ar":"لَا يَذْكُرُونَ ا@للّٰهَ اـِلَّا دَسَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or, accord. to Z, this is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dasama","text_ar":"دَسَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of rain: and, as related by Abu-d-Dardà, the words are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araDiytumo A_ino $abiEotumo","text_ar":"اَرَضِيتُمْ اـِنْ شَبِعْتُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmFA A^al~aA ta*okuruwna A@ll~`ha A_il~aA dasamFA","text_ar":"عَامًا اَلَّا تَذْكُرُونَ ا@للّٰهَ اـِلَّا دَسَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do ye approve, if ye be satisfied in your stomachs throughout a year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that ye should not praise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glorify, God, save a little?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it may denote commendation; so that the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA y*krwn All~`h Al~A dsmFA","text_ar":"لا يذكرون اللّٰه الّا دسمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, that praise, or glorification, is the stuffing of their hearts and of their mouths: and it may denote discommendation; as meaning that they praise, or glorify, little; from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadosiymu nuwnapi AlS~abiY~i","text_ar":"تَدْسِيمُ نُونَةِ الصَّبِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) the blackness denoted by this phrase being small in quantity: or, as some say, the meaning is, that they do not praise, or glorify, God for anything but eating, and the grease, or gravy, in their insides. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}